1
00:00:06,407 --> 00:00:07,425
You gotta be kidding me.

2
00:00:07,426 --> 00:00:08,760
I can't take you.

3
00:00:08,828 --> 00:00:10,762
Well, how many times
have I taken you to the airport?

4
00:00:10,830 --> 00:00:13,531
Matt has a soccer game tomorrow.
I have a report I have to finish.

5
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:15,500
It'll only take an hour.

6
00:00:16,836 --> 00:00:19,905
Fine. I'll call a cab.

7
00:00:19,973 --> 00:00:22,474
Oh, come on, Kyle.

8
00:00:24,843 --> 00:00:27,011
[Text message tone]

9
00:00:36,989 --> 00:00:39,089
[Sent tone]

10
00:00:41,592 --> 00:00:44,327
Kyle, I'm running out!

11
00:01:06,816 --> 00:01:08,316
[Car lock beep]

12
00:01:24,332 --> 00:01:25,566
Uhh!

13
00:01:39,647 --> 00:01:41,314
[Tires squealing]

14
00:01:45,085 --> 00:01:46,218
Come on, Rossi.

15
00:01:46,286 --> 00:01:47,653
I don't want to use them.

16
00:01:47,721 --> 00:01:50,322
I don't even understand you.
It's a vacation, Rossi.

17
00:01:50,356 --> 00:01:51,791
Everyone likes vacation.

18
00:01:51,858 --> 00:01:53,726
Vacations are overrated.

19
00:01:53,760 --> 00:01:55,460
Didn't you take a vacation
two years ago?

20
00:01:55,528 --> 00:01:57,897
Luckily, two days in
I was called back.

21
00:01:57,964 --> 00:02:00,131
Garcia: Yeah, and now
he's got 31 days.

22
00:02:00,199 --> 00:02:01,866
A month?

23
00:02:01,934 --> 00:02:03,467
You know, sunshine is an essential
source of vitamin D.

24
00:02:03,535 --> 00:02:05,103
You should go to Florida
and get some sunshine.

25
00:02:05,171 --> 00:02:06,537
That's for old guys.

26
00:02:06,605 --> 00:02:07,772
What about a safari
in Africa?

27
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:08,807
Too hot.

28
00:02:08,874 --> 00:02:10,241
Reid: How about Italy?
Too many relatives.

29
00:02:10,309 --> 00:02:11,576
You sound hermetic.

30
00:02:11,643 --> 00:02:14,045
No, Rossi just likes
his wine and stogies.

31
00:02:14,113 --> 00:02:16,180
And I go crazy
if I have nothing to do.

32
00:02:16,247 --> 00:02:18,148
You know, Rossi, if you don't
use 'em, you lose 'em.

33
00:02:18,216 --> 00:02:20,350
Thank you. This is what
I've been telling him.

34
00:02:20,418 --> 00:02:23,486
See this? This is my
"I don't care" face.

35
00:02:23,554 --> 00:02:25,255
That's your normal face.

36
00:02:25,323 --> 00:02:29,893
If I were you, I'd give your vacation
days away to a colleague in need.

37
00:02:29,961 --> 00:02:30,927
[Snaps fingers]

38
00:02:30,994 --> 00:02:33,262
Garcia, see how many people
in the Bureau

39
00:02:33,330 --> 00:02:35,832
have spouses in the military
serving overseas.

40
00:02:35,866 --> 00:02:38,835
I am on it.
Altruism is sexy.

41
00:02:38,902 --> 00:02:40,402
Yes, it is.

42
00:02:40,470 --> 00:02:41,971
Yes, sir.
Let's get started.

43
00:02:42,039 --> 00:02:43,606
All right, crime-fighters,

44
00:02:43,673 --> 00:02:45,808
last night, two victims,

45
00:02:45,876 --> 00:02:48,476
Brenda Wipley
and Mark Coleman

46
00:02:48,544 --> 00:02:50,011
were found murdered
hours apart,

47
00:02:50,079 --> 00:02:51,279
one in San Diego,
one in Los Angeles.

48
00:02:51,347 --> 00:02:53,314
They were blitz-attacked
and they were chained to a car

49
00:02:53,382 --> 00:02:55,650
where they were dragged alive
to their deaths.

50
00:02:55,718 --> 00:02:58,086
And the local P.D. does not believe
the victims knew each other.

51
00:02:58,154 --> 00:03:00,922
And both received similar
text messages last night

52
00:03:00,990 --> 00:03:02,823
from prepaid phones
asking them to meet.

53
00:03:02,891 --> 00:03:05,325
So our unsub's a friend
or at least pretends to be one.

54
00:03:05,393 --> 00:03:07,995
Based on how they were killed,
he wanted to see them suffer.

55
00:03:08,063 --> 00:03:09,230
Morgan: He's sadistic.

56
00:03:09,297 --> 00:03:11,198
Mm-hmm. And mission oriented.

57
00:03:11,266 --> 00:03:12,800
Dragging's usually
associated with hate crimes,

58
00:03:12,868 --> 00:03:14,735
but neither victim
was a minority nor gay.

59
00:03:14,803 --> 00:03:17,071
Actually, dragging is steeped
in English history.

60
00:03:17,139 --> 00:03:18,739
Back in the 11th Century,
drawing and quartering

61
00:03:18,806 --> 00:03:20,573
was a common form
of punishment, and in fact,

62
00:03:20,641 --> 00:03:21,722
they would also disembowel

63
00:03:21,747 --> 00:03:23,476
and behead the victims when
they were done with them.

64
00:03:23,477 --> 00:03:25,544
But that didn't happen here.

65
00:03:25,612 --> 00:03:28,214
Maybe this is just
a serial killer who crosses city lines.

66
00:03:28,282 --> 00:03:30,950
I don't know. Two victims in 3 hours?
That's a spree.

67
00:03:31,018 --> 00:03:32,852
Our unsub may claim
another victim soon.

68
00:03:32,920 --> 00:03:35,287
Which is why we're headed west.
We'll land in Orange County,

69
00:03:35,354 --> 00:03:37,790
half of us will go to San Diego,
the other half L.A.

70
00:03:37,857 --> 00:03:39,892
Wheels up in 30.

71
00:03:41,394 --> 00:03:43,095
Uhh!

72
00:03:45,899 --> 00:03:49,234
Wait. Wait. Come back!
What did I do to you?!

73
00:03:49,302 --> 00:03:51,969
Please don't do this!

74
00:03:52,037 --> 00:03:52,970
No!

75
00:03:53,038 --> 00:03:54,371
Oh, no, no!

76
00:03:56,092 --> 00:04:00,092
