77
00:04:00,117 --> 00:04:04,117
== sync, corrected by <font color="#00ff00">elderman</font> ==

78
00:04:04,142 --> 00:04:25,653
♪

79
00:04:30,844 --> 00:04:32,453
Rossi: Ralph Steadman wrote,

80
00:04:32,454 --> 00:04:35,089
"evil is always devising
more corrosive misery

81
00:04:35,157 --> 00:04:39,594
through man's restless need
to exact revenge out of his hate."

82
00:04:39,662 --> 00:04:41,663
All right, let's go
to victimology.

83
00:04:41,730 --> 00:04:44,064
Neither of the victims was
sexually assaulted or robbed.

84
00:04:44,132 --> 00:04:46,033
Well, Brenda was a teacher
and a mother of two.

85
00:04:46,101 --> 00:04:47,568
She went to meet a friend
that night.

86
00:04:47,636 --> 00:04:49,703
Mm-hmm. And her husband
backs the story.

87
00:04:49,771 --> 00:04:51,571
And the other victim,
Mark Coleman, was an addict.

88
00:04:51,639 --> 00:04:53,907
He was killed in the
parking lot of a drugstore

89
00:04:53,974 --> 00:04:55,909
around the corner from
the sober living house.

90
00:04:55,976 --> 00:04:59,279
A woman with no apparent addiction
and a tweaker in a sober living house?

91
00:04:59,347 --> 00:05:01,181
They probably don't know
each other.

92
00:05:01,248 --> 00:05:03,249
Garcia, did the unsub
call the victims

93
00:05:03,318 --> 00:05:06,118
on the disposable cells
prior to that night?

94
00:05:06,186 --> 00:05:08,521
Let's see. In the last
few weeks,

95
00:05:08,588 --> 00:05:11,390
he called each of the victims
over two times a day.

96
00:05:11,458 --> 00:05:13,492
That's not random.
It's hunting.

97
00:05:13,560 --> 00:05:15,093
Without phone transcripts,
it's going to be hard

98
00:05:15,161 --> 00:05:16,929
to understand what
the unsub's ruse was.

99
00:05:16,996 --> 00:05:18,497
Well, it ended pretty bad.

100
00:05:18,565 --> 00:05:20,865
Tying someone to the back
of a car is horrific

101
00:05:20,933 --> 00:05:23,668
and uncharacteristically
high-risk behavior.

102
00:05:23,736 --> 00:05:26,338
It was pure torture. Skin was
scraped off, bones were broken.

103
00:05:26,405 --> 00:05:27,939
That's about desecrating
the body.

104
00:05:28,006 --> 00:05:29,374
Well, our unsub is comfortable

105
00:05:29,442 --> 00:05:30,842
using chains and hitching
equipment.

106
00:05:30,909 --> 00:05:32,877
You know, the crimes could have
been committed to promote fear.

107
00:05:32,945 --> 00:05:35,380
All right, just--
can we rewind for a second?

108
00:05:35,448 --> 00:05:38,382
Is it possible to kill
someone in San Diego

109
00:05:38,450 --> 00:05:41,218
and then drive 2 1/2 hours
up to L.A.

110
00:05:41,285 --> 00:05:42,720
And then do it again?

111
00:05:42,787 --> 00:05:45,188
If you drove a V8 engine
with a single plane crankshaft

112
00:05:45,256 --> 00:05:46,789
80 miles per hour
in good traffic,

113
00:05:46,857 --> 00:05:49,091
you took the I-5 to the 405
to the 10 east,

114
00:05:49,159 --> 00:05:52,228
got off on La Cienega, went right
on Washington, north on Vermont,

115
00:05:52,295 --> 00:05:53,730
and then snuck up Selma
using the back alley,

116
00:05:53,797 --> 00:05:55,064
you could do it
in an hour, 42 minutes,

117
00:05:55,131 --> 00:05:56,733
and still have time
for tacos.

118
00:05:58,702 --> 00:05:59,635
Wow.

119
00:05:59,703 --> 00:06:00,770
Yeah.

120
00:06:00,838 --> 00:06:02,838
JJ, you and Morgan go to
the latest crime scene.

121
00:06:02,905 --> 00:06:05,273
Dave, you and Blake to San Diego
to the medical examiner's,

122
00:06:05,341 --> 00:06:07,075
and Reid and I
will go to the LAPD.

123
00:06:07,142 --> 00:06:10,679
[Indistinct chatter
and police radio]

124
00:06:10,747 --> 00:06:12,447
Officer: You gotta keep
the barricades back.

125
00:06:12,515 --> 00:06:13,982
JJ.

126
00:06:14,049 --> 00:06:15,650
The blood trail ends
about 3 blocks away

127
00:06:15,718 --> 00:06:17,185
where the body
was found.

128
00:06:17,253 --> 00:06:19,820
This is where he was
tied to the car.

129
00:06:19,855 --> 00:06:21,422
What's up
with the drugstore?

130
00:06:21,490 --> 00:06:23,758
It was closed Friday. They're
in the middle of a remodel.

131
00:06:23,825 --> 00:06:25,092
That's convenient.

132
00:06:25,159 --> 00:06:28,328
Yes. So is the fact
that the camera's not working.

133
00:06:28,397 --> 00:06:30,664
So the unsub
drags Mark over here,

134
00:06:30,732 --> 00:06:32,366
then blitz attacks him
from behind.

135
00:06:32,434 --> 00:06:34,133
Ok, if the killer knew
the drugstore was closed

136
00:06:34,201 --> 00:06:35,402
and the cameras
weren't working,

137
00:06:35,469 --> 00:06:36,536
he wasn't expecting
anyone here.

138
00:06:36,604 --> 00:06:37,970
And he scoped out
the nearby streets.

139
00:06:38,038 --> 00:06:39,539
He knew there'd be
low traffic,

140
00:06:39,607 --> 00:06:41,808
so he could drag
the victims without being caught.

141
00:06:41,876 --> 00:06:44,611
What if Mark
was falling off the wagon

142
00:06:44,678 --> 00:06:46,312
and he was meeting
his dealer?

143
00:06:46,380 --> 00:06:49,548
Right? Like the first victim

144
00:06:49,616 --> 00:06:51,216
also met the unsub
in a parking lot.

145
00:06:51,284 --> 00:06:52,918
Maybe she had
a drug habit, too.

146
00:06:52,985 --> 00:06:54,686
It's possible.
But either way,

147
00:06:54,754 --> 00:06:56,655
our unsub is highly
organized.

148
00:06:59,191 --> 00:07:01,727
[Cell phone rings]

149
00:07:02,595 --> 00:07:05,363
Hello?

150
00:07:05,398 --> 00:07:07,698
Oh, hi.

151
00:07:07,766 --> 00:07:09,767
I can't do it today.

152
00:07:09,835 --> 00:07:12,202
I know.
I'm really sorry.

153
00:07:12,270 --> 00:07:13,671
Next week.

154
00:07:13,739 --> 00:07:15,406
Promise.

155
00:07:18,043 --> 00:07:20,077
[Text message tone]

156
00:07:22,413 --> 00:07:25,348
Me, too.

157
00:07:25,416 --> 00:07:29,619
Name the place.

158
00:07:33,825 --> 00:07:36,493
Officer: The desk sergeant.

159
00:07:36,561 --> 00:07:37,793
[Indistinct chatter]

160
00:07:37,861 --> 00:07:39,862
Hi, I'm Detective Pratt.
You must be SSA Hotchner.

161
00:07:39,930 --> 00:07:41,396
I am. This is
Dr. Spencer Reid.

162
00:07:41,465 --> 00:07:42,431
Pleasure.

163
00:07:42,499 --> 00:07:43,999
Well, I talked to San Diego PD.

164
00:07:44,067 --> 00:07:47,570
They sent over everything on
the first victim Brenda Wipley's case.

165
00:07:47,637 --> 00:07:49,972
And Mr. Coleman's updated
file's on the conference room table.

166
00:07:50,039 --> 00:07:51,373
I'll start looking them over.

167
00:07:51,441 --> 00:07:52,641
Now, should we notify
the press

168
00:07:52,709 --> 00:07:54,141
that we're looking
for a spree killer?

169
00:07:54,209 --> 00:07:55,710
Not until we know exactly
what we're looking for.

170
00:07:55,778 --> 00:07:57,378
Ok. You guys can set up
right in here.

171
00:07:57,446 --> 00:07:59,447
[Text message tone]
Thank you.

172
00:08:02,184 --> 00:08:04,552
Morgan and JJ think
that maybe our second victim Mark

173
00:08:04,620 --> 00:08:06,721
went to meet a drug dealer.
Have you gotten the tox screens back?

174
00:08:06,789 --> 00:08:09,090
Neither of the victims
had drugs in their system.

175
00:08:09,157 --> 00:08:10,757
It doesn't mean they didn't
go meet a dealer.

176
00:08:10,825 --> 00:08:13,159
But a drug dealer doesn't call you
twice a day for two weeks.

177
00:08:13,227 --> 00:08:14,361
Usually you call him.

178
00:08:14,428 --> 00:08:15,896
[Cell phone rings]

179
00:08:15,964 --> 00:08:17,230
Go ahead, Garcia.

180
00:08:17,331 --> 00:08:20,100
The path of my cyber sleuthing
has had majestic results.

181
00:08:20,167 --> 00:08:23,670
Digging into victim number
two's past,

182
00:08:23,738 --> 00:08:26,038
it turns out meth isn't the only thing
Mark Coleman had done.

183
00:08:26,106 --> 00:08:27,707
He also changed his last name.

184
00:08:27,774 --> 00:08:28,774
From what?

185
00:08:28,842 --> 00:08:31,343
Logan. And that's where
the plot thickens

186
00:08:31,411 --> 00:08:32,344
like a bad pudding.

187
00:08:32,412 --> 00:08:34,847
So when Mark was a junior
in college,

188
00:08:34,915 --> 00:08:37,216
he gets picked up by police
on a drug charge.

189
00:08:37,283 --> 00:08:39,218
They find some articles
of clothing

190
00:08:39,285 --> 00:08:42,554
of a missing 8-year-old girl
named Kelly Taylor in his car.

191
00:08:42,622 --> 00:08:44,723
They are covered
with Mark's DNA.

192
00:08:44,790 --> 00:08:46,791
After a lengthy interrogation,

193
00:08:46,859 --> 00:08:49,360
he confesses to sexually
assaulting her,

194
00:08:49,428 --> 00:08:52,296
but denies killing her, and
because her body was never found,

195
00:08:52,364 --> 00:08:53,999
they couldn't link him
to the disappearance.

196
00:08:54,066 --> 00:08:55,534
What's he been doing
since he got out?

197
00:08:55,601 --> 00:08:56,868
Eating hamburgers.

198
00:08:56,936 --> 00:08:58,301
He got released a month ago.

199
00:08:58,369 --> 00:09:00,504
Since then he's worked at 3
different fast food joints.

200
00:09:00,572 --> 00:09:02,072
Send me everything
you've got on the case.

201
00:09:02,140 --> 00:09:03,741
I'll have Reid
go talk to the family.

202
00:09:03,808 --> 00:09:05,643
Yeah.

203
00:09:13,984 --> 00:09:15,351
Outside.

204
00:09:15,419 --> 00:09:17,086
I was having my soup.

205
00:09:17,154 --> 00:09:18,454
Now.

206
00:09:18,522 --> 00:09:21,824
Thanks. Garcia was only
able to give away

207
00:09:21,892 --> 00:09:23,674
25 of my vacation days

208
00:09:23,699 --> 00:09:25,394
to employees with loved ones
in Afghanistan.

209
00:09:25,395 --> 00:09:27,329
Well, great. Now you just
have to figure out

210
00:09:27,397 --> 00:09:30,699
what to do with
the remaining 6.

211
00:09:30,767 --> 00:09:32,400
Hey. I'm Dr. Mathis.

212
00:09:32,468 --> 00:09:34,269
I heard it took
the L.A. M.E. 4 hours

213
00:09:34,336 --> 00:09:36,638
to find the second
victim's entire body.

214
00:09:36,706 --> 00:09:38,674
Yeah, he was spread
all over the place.

215
00:09:38,741 --> 00:09:41,342
Well, victim one had it
easy by comparison.

216
00:09:41,410 --> 00:09:42,945
She was dragged postmortem.

217
00:09:43,012 --> 00:09:45,113
We thought she was alive
at first.

218
00:09:45,181 --> 00:09:47,114
No. She died from
a series of blows to the head.

219
00:09:47,182 --> 00:09:49,516
So the unsub was scared
on his first kill,

220
00:09:49,585 --> 00:09:51,852
then two hours later
when he got his second victim,

221
00:09:51,920 --> 00:09:55,022
his confidence suddenly
evolved.

222
00:09:55,090 --> 00:09:56,857
That's a pretty quick
evolution.

223
00:09:56,925 --> 00:09:59,860
And therein lies the problem.

224
00:10:02,563 --> 00:10:04,631
So I talked to victim
number two's father.

225
00:10:04,699 --> 00:10:06,466
He said as far as he knew,
no one was trying

226
00:10:06,533 --> 00:10:07,701
to get back at Mark
for the rape.

227
00:10:07,768 --> 00:10:09,368
He got out of jail
last month.

228
00:10:09,436 --> 00:10:12,371
He was getting out more, exercising,
trying to get on with his life.

229
00:10:12,439 --> 00:10:15,642
Well, I just compared photos
from the first and second crime scenes.

230
00:10:15,710 --> 00:10:17,643
The cars used to drag
were different.

231
00:10:17,711 --> 00:10:18,978
Maybe the killer
switched cars?

232
00:10:19,045 --> 00:10:20,679
Or we're looking
at two unsubs.

233
00:10:20,747 --> 00:10:22,047
What did you
and Morgan find?

234
00:10:22,115 --> 00:10:23,616
Well, at both crime scenes,

235
00:10:23,683 --> 00:10:26,719
the nearby stores were either closed
or being remodeled,

236
00:10:26,786 --> 00:10:28,954
so the killer would have
had to scope the area,

237
00:10:29,022 --> 00:10:30,889
lure and drag the victim
without being caught.

238
00:10:30,957 --> 00:10:33,225
This guy has a lot to do.
So the question remains,

239
00:10:33,292 --> 00:10:35,227
how can you do that
twice in one night

240
00:10:35,294 --> 00:10:37,129
in cities over
100 miles apart?

241
00:10:37,196 --> 00:10:39,564
Two unsubs would explain
the evolution in M.O.

242
00:10:39,632 --> 00:10:41,833
What did Rossi and Blake say?

243
00:10:41,867 --> 00:10:43,301
The first victim Brenda
was dragged postmortem.

244
00:10:43,369 --> 00:10:44,603
The second victim
was alive.

245
00:10:44,670 --> 00:10:47,405
So we're most likely looking
at one unsub who's hesitant

246
00:10:47,473 --> 00:10:51,108
and another one
who actually enjoys it.

247
00:10:52,177 --> 00:10:53,810
What do you mean,
you killed her first?

248
00:10:53,878 --> 00:10:56,347
I just couldn't do it
while she was still alive.

249
