00:34:49,355 --> 00:34:51,456
When Mark died,
I needed to cover my tracks.

761
00:34:51,524 --> 00:34:54,626
Uh...oh. Oh. Oh.

762
00:34:54,693 --> 00:34:57,093
It's right here.
I remember.

763
00:34:57,162 --> 00:34:59,095
Right...here.

764
00:34:59,164 --> 00:35:01,665
Start digging.

765
00:35:05,537 --> 00:35:09,606
The landlord says this is
Jason's storage closet.

766
00:35:16,213 --> 00:35:17,880
It looks like
my storage unit.

767
00:35:17,947 --> 00:35:21,083
My husband has so much crap,
it's not funny.

768
00:35:21,151 --> 00:35:23,419
Is it hard being in a relationship
with someone overseas?

769
00:35:23,487 --> 00:35:24,820
We make it work.

770
00:35:24,888 --> 00:35:27,323
Working for Doctors Without Borders
is a very noble cause.

771
00:35:27,391 --> 00:35:30,292
I would imagine you guys have
an epistolary novel by now, though.

772
00:35:30,359 --> 00:35:33,228
We stick to Skype.
It's modern.

773
00:35:33,296 --> 00:35:35,263
When we're together,
it's like we're dating,

774
00:35:35,331 --> 00:35:38,900
and when we're not,
I get stuff done.

775
00:35:38,967 --> 00:35:41,903
Look at this.

776
00:35:45,840 --> 00:35:47,741
Fresh loam soil.

777
00:35:47,809 --> 00:35:49,276
Usually found near
plains and streams.

778
00:35:49,344 --> 00:35:50,511
Either he was
just camping...

779
00:35:50,579 --> 00:35:52,246
Or used it
to move the body.

780
00:35:52,314 --> 00:35:54,682
Jason finds out
his friends are killed,

781
00:35:54,749 --> 00:35:57,518
he might take precautions.

782
00:35:59,387 --> 00:36:01,387
What is taking so long?

783
00:36:01,455 --> 00:36:03,590
I'm almost there.

784
00:36:03,657 --> 00:36:04,591
Hurry up!

785
00:36:04,658 --> 00:36:06,659
[Thud]
Oh...

786
00:36:06,727 --> 00:36:07,660
[Thud]

787
00:36:07,728 --> 00:36:11,564
Oh. Oh...

788
00:36:27,212 --> 00:36:29,146
There it is.

789
00:36:29,881 --> 00:36:33,417
That's just a skull.

790
00:36:33,485 --> 00:36:35,519
Where's the rest
of my daughter?

791
00:36:35,587 --> 00:36:39,022
We have a few more
holes to dig.

792
00:36:40,725 --> 00:36:42,926
You cut up my baby?

793
00:36:45,496 --> 00:36:47,197
That was my idea, too.

794
00:36:47,265 --> 00:36:49,299
Oh, my God!

795
00:36:49,367 --> 00:36:51,001
Oh, my God.
[Laughing]

796
00:36:51,069 --> 00:36:52,803
Oh, my God!
Oh, my God!

797
00:36:52,871 --> 00:36:56,072
Oh, my God!
Oh, my God!

798
00:36:56,140 --> 00:37:00,276
[Screaming]

799
00:37:07,317 --> 00:37:10,853
There's loam soil surrounding
some Southern California beaches

800
00:37:10,921 --> 00:37:13,889
and also loam soil around
some parks in the area.

801
00:37:13,956 --> 00:37:15,690
What areas are near
running trails?

802
00:37:15,758 --> 00:37:18,426
Uh, there is a trail
in the Hollywood Hills area

803
00:37:18,494 --> 00:37:19,906
that is lousy with loam soil.

804
00:37:19,931 --> 00:37:22,415
And I'm sending Morgan
and Rossi to the location now.

805
00:37:39,881 --> 00:37:41,982
Over here.

806
00:37:49,657 --> 00:37:51,591
They got him.

807
00:37:51,659 --> 00:37:54,761
We've got officers at Ellen
and Darlene's homes

808
00:37:54,829 --> 00:37:56,530
just in case
they come back.

809
00:37:56,597 --> 00:37:59,299
And have them check the airports,
bus stations, train stations, everything.

810
00:37:59,367 --> 00:38:01,634
I'll also put an APB out
along the coast.

811
00:38:01,702 --> 00:38:04,069
Garcia cross-checked
the trophies we found at Jason's,

812
00:38:04,137 --> 00:38:06,071
and they match articles
from 3 different missing children.

813
00:38:06,139 --> 00:38:07,473
And have officers
excavate the area

814
00:38:07,541 --> 00:38:09,041
around where
Jason's body was found.

815
00:38:09,108 --> 00:38:10,309
There may be
more bodies there.

816
00:38:10,377 --> 00:38:12,044
I'm on it.

817
00:38:12,111 --> 00:38:13,979
Blake:
At least we got Jason.

818
00:38:14,047 --> 00:38:16,215
He could have kept
killing forever.

819
00:38:16,282 --> 00:38:18,316
And the women
just get away.

820
00:38:18,384 --> 00:38:20,452
Hmm. For now.

821
00:38:21,620 --> 00:38:23,888
You ok?

822
00:38:23,956 --> 00:38:25,323
Yeah.

823
00:38:28,160 --> 00:38:30,362
Yeah.

824
00:38:32,664 --> 00:38:37,000
[Chatter, laughter]

825
00:38:41,373 --> 00:38:43,440
So now what?

826
00:38:43,508 --> 00:38:44,441
Well,

827
00:38:44,509 --> 00:38:47,578
um, we're gonna split up.

828
00:38:47,645 --> 00:38:49,879
I might keep heading south.

829
00:38:49,946 --> 00:38:52,014
You'd do good here.

830
00:38:52,082 --> 00:38:53,516
Yeah. You're right.

831
00:38:53,584 --> 00:38:57,387
I think it's better
if we don't stay together.

832
00:38:59,656 --> 00:39:02,492
You know what I don't get?

833
00:39:02,526 --> 00:39:05,861
How this was so easy for you.

834
00:39:05,928 --> 00:39:07,161
How so?

835
00:39:07,229 --> 00:39:09,163
We had to kill 5 people.

836
00:39:09,231 --> 00:39:10,599
Our deal was just for two.

837
00:39:10,666 --> 00:39:12,467
That's not what
I'm talking about.

838
00:39:12,535 --> 00:39:15,570
Does it bother you that none
of this took the hurt away?

839
00:39:15,638 --> 00:39:18,440
I never thought it would.

840
00:39:18,508 --> 00:39:19,941
Then why did we do it?

841
00:39:20,009 --> 00:39:24,211
Because somebody
has to pay, ok?

842
00:39:24,279 --> 00:39:26,346
I don't care
what anybody says.

843
00:39:26,415 --> 00:39:28,883
Actions have consequences.

844
00:39:28,950 --> 00:39:31,218
Maybe not at trial.

845
00:39:31,286 --> 00:39:33,287
Maybe not in jail.

846
00:39:33,354 --> 00:39:35,355
Come on.
Admit it, Darlene,

847
00:39:35,424 --> 00:39:37,290
this gave you
a reason to live.

848
00:39:37,357 --> 00:39:39,859
That's what I was hoping.

849
00:39:39,927 --> 00:39:44,030
But it just made me
feel more...

850
00:39:45,966 --> 00:39:48,134
more nothing.

851
00:39:48,201 --> 00:39:50,570
Then you're a wuss.

852
00:39:53,406 --> 00:39:55,974
I'm gonna go get us
something cold to drink.

853
00:39:56,042 --> 00:40:00,879
Wait. I diss you and you care
if I'm thirsty?

854
00:40:00,947 --> 00:40:04,382
Huh. You gotta start
thinking about yourself, honey.

855
00:40:04,451 --> 00:40:06,251
That's the game.

856
00:40:16,127 --> 00:40:17,728
Dollars ok?

857
00:40:17,796 --> 00:40:19,564
Gracias.

858
00:40:46,523 --> 00:40:48,056
Ellen Russel?

859
00:40:51,127 --> 00:40:52,862
How'd you find me?

860
00:40:52,896 --> 00:40:57,398
Darlene never unpacked
her daughter's bags from this trip.

861
00:40:57,466 --> 00:41:01,002
And I took a wild guess.

862
00:41:01,069 --> 00:41:04,772
So what happens now?

863
00:41:06,141 --> 00:41:09,176
What happens now
is you go back to the U.S.

864
00:41:09,244 --> 00:41:13,881
I take 6 days off
that I don't even want.

865
00:41:13,948 --> 00:41:17,183
Where's Darlene?

866
00:41:17,251 --> 00:41:19,285
She's long gone.

867
00:41:19,320 --> 00:41:23,690
Personally, I have
mixed feelings about that one.

868
00:41:24,926 --> 00:41:27,895
But we'll get her, too.

869
00:41:29,663 --> 00:41:31,497
Levantese.

870
00:42:06,197 --> 00:42:11,334
[Speaking spanish]

871
00:42:11,402 --> 00:42:13,537
...a Los Estados Unidos.

872
00:42:13,605 --> 00:42:15,238
Rossi: Thanks for your help.

873
00:42:34,490 --> 00:42:36,725
Rossi: Paul Brown once said,

874
00:42:36,793 --> 00:42:39,427
"If you win, say nothing.

875
00:42:39,495 --> 00:42:42,664
If you lose, say less."

